<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="88" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,618,715]" pageId="7" pageNumber="88">
The largest family of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1839" box="[424,545,618,643]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Plecoptera</taxonomicName>
, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[614,706,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Perlidae</taxonomicName>
include&gt;1,000 described species distributed throughout the Neotropical, Holarctic, Oriental, and Afrotropical regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Fochetti, R. &amp; Tierno de Figueroa, J. M." box="[817,1233,654,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="88" pagination="365 - 377" refId="ref7465" refString="Fochetti, R. &amp; Tierno de Figueroa, J. M. (2008) Global diversity of stoneflies (Plecoptera; Insecta) in freshwater. Hydrobiologia, 595, 365 - 377. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10750 - 007 - 9031 - 3" type="journal article" year="2008">Fochetti &amp; Tierno de Figueroa 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The Neotropical fauna of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[250,342,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Perlidae</taxonomicName>
includes 10 genera and approximately 390 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich, C. G." box="[926,1116,690,715]" pageId="7" pageNumber="88" pagination="118 - 205" refId="ref7972" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2010 a) Catalogue of Neotropical Plecoptera. Illiesia, 6, 118 - 205." type="journal article" year="2010">Froehlich 2010a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
